cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about aspect-level sentiment classification, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and sentiment analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Within cs.CL, the paper focuses on machine learning models, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper proposes a novel approach that uses graph convolutional networks (GCN), which is a type of neural network architecture, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category. The paper also involves text classification and information retrieval, so cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category. Finally, the paper uses a bidirectional attention mechanism, which is a type of neural network architecture commonly used in natural language processing, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category.
